sqlc-gen-python-arche
=====================

This project is a fork of sqlc-gen-better-python by Rayakame:

    https://github.com/rayakame/sqlc-gen-better-python

The upstream project is licensed under the MIT License (see LICENSE), and its
copyright is retained. This fork adds a SQLAlchemy-async + Pydantic code path
and nullability-inference hardening on top of that base; the bulk of the
generator — model and query emitters, driver abstraction, inflection, and type
machinery — is the work of the upstream authors.

The upstream project, and this fork through it, draws on the wider sqlc
ecosystem:

  - sqlc-dev/sqlc            https://github.com/sqlc-dev/sqlc
      The SQL compiler and the plugin SDK (plugin-sdk-go) this plugin targets.
  - sqlc-dev/sqlc-gen-python https://github.com/sqlc-dev/sqlc-gen-python
  - sqlc-dev/sqlc-gen-kotlin https://github.com/sqlc-dev/sqlc-gen-kotlin
      Prior-art code generators that informed the emitter design.
  - sqlc-dev/sqlc-gen-go     https://github.com/sqlc-dev/sqlc-gen-go
  - tandemdude/sqlc-gen-java https://github.com/tandemdude/sqlc-gen-java
      References for building a sqlc WASM plugin.

Third-party Go dependencies (see go.mod / go.sum for exact versions):

  - github.com/jinzhu/inflection         (MIT)   singularization
  - github.com/sqlc-dev/plugin-sdk-go    (MIT)   sqlc plugin SDK

